const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What's a steam-jacketed kettle?",
    a: "Double-walled cooking vessel: outer wall steam jacket, inner cooking chamber. Steam injected between the walls heats the cooking surface indirectly. Used for soups, sauces, stocks, and bulk-cook applications. Different from direct-fire pots (more even heat, no scorching) and from steamers (a kettle holds liquid food; a steamer cooks solids in pans)."
  },
  {
    q: "Self-contained vs direct-steam kettle: which do I have?",
    a: "Self-contained means built-in steam generator, plug-in (electric) or gas-fired. No building steam connection. Most common LA installations (Cleveland TKET, Groen INA). Direct-steam connects to a building steam supply (60+ PSI). Larger institutional applications: Cleveland KGL, Legion, Market Forge."
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my kettle take longer to heat lately?",
    a: "Most likely steam jacket scale buildup. LA hard water leaves mineral deposits inside the steam jacket, reducing heat transfer efficiency. Annual descaling $400 to $700 restores performance. Without descaling, eventual heating element burnout leads to $1,500+ emergency repair."
  },
  {
    q: "My tilting kettle is stuck and won't tilt smoothly.",
    a: "Tilt mechanism wear. Hand-crank tilt is gear wear (year 8 to 12 typical), $440 to $680 replacement. Power-tilt is electric motor failure, $680 to $980. We service both. Hand-crank service is more common in LA-area kitchens; power-tilt is more common on premium institutional installations."
  },
  {
    q: "Pressure relief valve testing: really required annually?",
    a: "Yes, safety critical. The pressure relief valve prevents over-pressurization of the steam jacket. Annual testing is required for insurance compliance and safety. Annual test verification plus replacement if it fails runs $290 to $540. Most LA shops avoid pressure equipment service due to liability; we don't."
  },
  {
    q: "Cleveland TKET vs Groen INA: which is better?",
    a: "Welbilt sister brands, similar quality, similar pricing. Cleveland TKET has dominant US market share, which means better parts availability. Groen INA has identical engineering quality (same parent corporation) and slight pricing advantage occasionally. Both fully serviceable; parts logistics similar via the Welbilt network."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you service direct-steam kettles connected to building steam supply?",
    a: "Yes. Cleveland KGL, Legion, and Market Forge direct-steam kettles serviced. The building steam supply system itself (boiler) is a separate specialty trade. We service the kettle-side connection, valves, and internal components."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. Cleveland, Groen, Vulcan, Legion, and Market Forge component warranties (where applicable through manufacturer authorized networks) processed separately. BHGS #A49573 and BBB A+."
  }
];

